{#
/**
 * @file Tables!
 * Documenting Table Examples from Tailwind.
 *
 * Available variables:
 * - table.header: [array] A list of table headers from _data/tables.yaml
 * - table.content: [array] A list of table content from _data/tables.yaml
 *
 * @see https://tailwindcss.com/docs/table-layout
 */
#}

<div class="container">
  <div class="row-auto">
    <div class="sm:mt-5">
      <h1 class="mb-3">Tables</h1>
      <div class="mb-3 p-3 bg-gray-100 border border-black border-lg">
        <p class="text-base">Documentation and examples for opt-in styling of tables (given their prevelant use in JavaScript plugins) with Tailwind.</p>
        <div><a href="https://tailwindcss.com/docs/table-layout/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="block text-sm mt-2">Tailwind Documentation</a></div>
      </div>
      <hr>

      <h2>Examples</h2>
      <p class="pb-2">Quickly create a table style with the <code>.table-auto</code> or <code>.table-fixed</code> class as <code>&lt;table class="table-auto"&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;table class="table-fixed"&gt;</code>.</p>

      <h3 class="py-2">Auto</h3>
      <p class="pb-2">Use <code>.table-auto</code> to allow the table to automatically size columns to fit the contents of the cell.</p>

      <div class="p-4 border">
        <table class="table-auto w-full">
          <thead class="text-left border-b">
          <tr>
            <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-2">#</th>
            {% for header in table.header %}
              <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-2">{{ header }}</th>
            {% endfor %}
          </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
          {% for content in table.content %}
            <tr class="border-b">
              <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-2 text-left">{{ loop.index }}</th>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">{{ content.first_name }}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">{{ content.last_name }}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">@{{ content.username }}</td>
            </tr>
          {% endfor %}
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <caption>This caption example was created with <code>&lt;caption&gt;&lt;/caption&gt;</code>.</caption>
      </div>

      <h3 class="pb-2 pt-5">Fixed</h3>
      <p class="pb-2">Use <code>.table-fixed</code> to allow the table to ignore the content and use fixed widths for columns. The width of the first row will set the column widths for the whole table.</p>
      <div class="p-4 border">
        <table class="table-auto w-full">
          <thead class="text-left border-b">
          <tr>
            <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-2 w-1/2">#</th>
            {% for header in table.header %}
              <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-2 w-1/4">{{ header }}</th>
            {% endfor %}
          </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
          {% for content in table.content %}
            <tr class="border-b">
              <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-2 text-left">{{ loop.index }}</th>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">{{ content.first_name }}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">{{ content.last_name }}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">@{{ content.username }}</td>
            </tr>
          {% endfor %}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="pb-2 pt-5">Styling tables examples</h2>
      <p>As easy as adding Tailwind's utility classes like <code>bg-gray-800</code> and <code>text-white</code> to the table and/or its elements. For example, <code>&lt;table class="bg-gray-800 text-white"&gt;</code>!</p>
      <div class="p-4 border">
        <table class="table-auto w-full bg-gray-800 text-white">
          <thead class="text-left border-b">
          <tr>
            <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-2">#</th>
            {% for header in table.header %}
              <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-2">{{ header }}</th>
            {% endfor %}
          </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
          {% for content in table.content %}
            <tr class="border-b text-left">
              <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-2">{{ loop.index }}</th>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">{{ content.first_name }}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">{{ content.last_name }}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">@{{ content.username }}</td>
            </tr>
          {% endfor %}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h3 class="pb-2 pt-5">Striped Rows</h3>
      <div class="p-4 border">
        <table class="table-auto w-full">
          <thead class="text-left border-b">
          <tr>
            <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-2">#</th>
            {% for header in table.header %}
              <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-2">{{ header }}</th>
            {% endfor %}
          </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
          {% for content in table.content %}
            <tr class="border-b {{ loop.index is not divisible by(2) ? 'bg-gray-100' }}">
              <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-2 text-left">{{ loop.index }}</th>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">{{ content.first_name }}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">{{ content.last_name }}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">@{{ content.username }}</td>
            </tr>
          {% endfor %}
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <br>
        <table class="table-auto w-full">
          <thead class="text-left text-white bg-gray-800">
          <tr>
            <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-2">#</th>
            {% for header in table.header %}
              <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-2">{{ header }}</th>
            {% endfor %}
          </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
          {% for content in table.content %}
            <tr class="text-white {{ loop.index is not divisible by(2) ? 'bg-gray-700' : 'bg-gray-800' }}">
              <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-2 text-left">{{ loop.index }}</th>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">{{ content.first_name }}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">{{ content.last_name }}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">@{{ content.username }}</td>
            </tr>
          {% endfor %}
          </tbody>
        </table>

      </div>

      <h3 class="pb-2 pt-5">Hoverable rows</h3>
      <p>
        Add <code>.hover:</code> pseudo classes on elements to enable a hover state within a <code>&lt;table&gt;</code>.
        <code>&lt;tr class="hover:bg-gray-100"&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;tr class="hover:text-black"&gt;</code>
      </p>
      <div class="p-4 border">
        <table class="table-auto w-full">
          <thead class="text-left border-b">
          <tr>
            <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-2">#</th>
            {% for header in table.header %}
              <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-2">{{ header }}</th>
            {% endfor %}
          </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
          {% for content in table.content %}
            <tr class="border-b hover:bg-gray-100">
              <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-2 text-left">{{ loop.index }}</th>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">{{ content.first_name }}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">{{ content.last_name }}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">@{{ content.username }}</td>
            </tr>
          {% endfor %}
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <br>
        <table class="table-auto w-full bg-gray-800 text-white">
          <thead class="text-left border-b">
          <tr>
            <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-2">#</th>
            {% for header in table.header %}
              <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-2">{{ header }}</th>
            {% endfor %}
          </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
          {% for content in table.content %}
            <tr class="border-b text-left hover:bg-gray-700">
              <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-2">{{ loop.index }}</th>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">{{ content.first_name }}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">{{ content.last_name }}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">@{{ content.username }}</td>
            </tr>
          {% endfor %}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
